text: in this demo we will show you how to
manage reports before managing reports
ensure you have the saved reports and
admin permission enabled in your
security profile once you have logged
into the Amazon connect instance you
will be redirected to the homepage in
the Le hand sidebar go to the graph icon
to expand the analytics and optimization
menu and select saved
reports to view all the reports select
the all reports tab once loaded you can
search for a particular report or use
the filter options you can filter by
report type which you can select either
dashboard real-time metrics historical
metrics or log in/ logout reports or you
can filter by the publish state or
lastly by the report Creator by typing
in their username for this demo let's
search for the report called
demo to delete reports select the
reports by using the check boxes on the
left and click remove in the top right
hand
corner now we can see the demo report is
no longer
visible with managing reports it
provides individuals easy access to
locate and view reports it also allows
removing of old reports that are no
longer required this encourages an
organized reporting environment keeping
the most relevant up-to-date and
accurate reports necessary for
evaluating contact center strategies
such as forecasting and Staffing plans
thank you for joining me in this demo to
learn how to manage reports
